  "time_ut": 1661329668,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dca, \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4 \u0dbd\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Objection from the Secretary of Potthu about Cope, Kopa appointments",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Sagara Kariyawasam, Secretary of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, has strongly objected to the proposals for the appointment of MPs to the positions of COP and COPA committee chairpersons outside the standing orders of the Parliament in the Parliamentary Affairs Committee meeting.",
        "He has pointed out here that the Samagi Jana Balawegaya party has proposed the names of two members of the party for the posts of chairman before the formation of those committees and it is not possible to do so according to the standing orders of the parliament.",
        "Mr. Kariyawasam has stated that it is clearly stated in the parliamentary standing orders that the committees should be formed first and then the chairman should be elected by the majority of the members.",
        "The chief organizer of the opposition, Mr. Lakshman Kiriella, who has presented the matter at this time, has stated that the speaker agreed to give the positions of the two committee chairpersons to the opposition in a previous parliamentary committee meeting.",
        "He further said that since there are notes of that meeting, he will ask the Speaker to act according to the decision taken that day.",
        "Before this, two members of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna held the positions of COP and COPA committee chairpersons.",
        "Professor Charitha Herath acted as the chairman of the COPE Committee and Professor Tissa Witharana acted as the chairman of the COPE Committee.",
        "With the termination of the second session of the Ninth Parliament, nearly seventy parliamentary committees, including COP and COPA, were abolished."
      ],
